RADIATION FLUX

En Fr

Radiation Environments

Sources of radiation include galactic cosmic rays, solar energy particles, and the Earth's radiation belt.

Deep Space

Deep space up to 300,000 particles/cm2/h, mainly protons with some particles and heavier ions.

Geosynchronous Orbit

Up to 500,000 particles/cm2/h, mainly electrons and protons.

Low Earth Orbit

Up to 100,000 particles/cm2/h, mainly protons and electrons.

Airplane Altitude

6000-9000 neutrons/cm2/h.

Ground Level

10-15 neutrons/cm2/h, ~ 60 muons/cm2/h.
